Package com.github.actionfx.core.method

Class ActionFXMethodInvocation

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.github.actionfx.core.method.ActionFXMethodInvocation
  • public class ActionFXMethodInvocation
extends java.lang.Object
    Convenience class for calling a method that can contain ActionFX annotations (like AFXRequiresUserConfirmation or method argument annotations like AFXControlValue.

    This class is used within the ActionFX framework for calling AFXOnAction annotated methods, however, it can be also used in application code, in case an "onAction" property event handler needs to be programmatically set by the developer.

    Author:
    koster

    • Constructor Detail

      • ActionFXMethodInvocation

        public ActionFXMethodInvocation​(java.lang.Object instance,
                                java.lang.String methodName,
                                java.lang.Object... arguments)
        Constructor receiving all required information including the methodName as a string for issuing a method invocation. Take care when using this constructor as the methodName might not exist or methods with that name might be ambiguous for the supplied arguments.
        Parameters:
        instance - the instance holding the method
        methodName - the method name itself
        arguments - the arguments that shall be passed to the method. Please note that there is an internal type-matching based on assigning the supplied arguments to the parameters of the method. The actual method can have additional parameter that are e.g. annotated by AFXControlValue that is internally looked up and of course, does not need to be provided as part of arguments.

The actual method can have additional parameter that are e.g. annotated by AFXControlValue that is internally looked up and of course, does not need to be provided as part of arguments.

        public <T> void callAsync​(java.util.function.Consumer<T> consumer)
        Performs an asynchronous method call, where the return value of the method is passed on to the supplied Consumer. The consumer is guaranteed to be executed inside the JavaFX-thread.
        Type Parameters:
        T - the return type
